<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.2. ">Pre-Requisites </h2>
<p>
    To login as an agent, we should have Sandbox access for the required test environment. We have two types of Agents
    L1 &amp; L2. L1 Agent can login to the Sandbox URL and create a Return Request for Stock Rotation. L2 Agent can view
    the cases assigned to them and can change the case owner.
</p>
<p>
    <strong> Sandbox (IAO QA) Link: </strong> <a href="https://isvc--isvcqa25.sandbox.my.salesforce.com/"> <strong>
            https://isvc--isvciaoqa.sandbox.my.salesforce.com/ </strong> </a>
</p>
<p>
    Access related issues, Contact: @Indus ISVC GRL R4C
</p>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.3. ">Login to CRM R4C System</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Enter the sandbox URL in the browser and login as an L1 Agent with your user credentials.</li>
    <li>After we login to the system, we will be able to see the app “Return for Credit ”, and “ Home” Tab .</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="f41ef451-2ae1-faeb-5f65-8e3c38bb0ba8" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>If ‘ Return for Credit ’ a pp is not displayed directly after login , then click on App launcher ( nine dots
            ) , search for “ R eturn for credit” and select first option.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.4. ">Case creation</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Select ‘Contact’ from the ‘Navigation items/ Menu’ dropdown</li>
    <li>Select a contact from the list view of contacts to open corresponding contact record.</li>
    <li>In the contact detail page, we can see “Create R4C Case” link &amp; “New R4C Case” Button, click on one of them.
    </li>
    <li>When Clicking on a contact hyperlink the page opens in a new tab and if clicked on the button then the “Step1
        Dialog box for Service type selection “is opened. “ Tech nical” is selected by default, Agent needs to select
        Admin for Admin Service Type.</li>
    <li>The New R4C Case subtab will be opened after clicking on the Create button. Fill in the Request header details
        &amp; Collection Details.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.5. ">SAP Blocks scenarios</h2>
<p>
    Before a Sold To, Payer or Ship To can be used on a case, R4C checks Export Compliance, Order, Billing and
    Delivery blocks at CMF and Sales Area level. Block values, hard-stop behavior, and how Case creation differs
    from Case edit are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Block Scenarios" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for the block rules.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Admin Intake:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Case creation: any Sold To CMF, Sales Area or Ship To CMF/Sales Area with a hard block is excluded from its
        respective selection dropdown; a Payer-level block surfaces as an error toast on Sold To selection.</li>
    <li>Case edit: a hard block present at Sold To CMF, Sales Area, Payer or Ship To level blocks the Edit action
        with an error toast.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.6. ">Request Header Details </h2>
<ul>
    <li>User should fill in all the mandatory fields which are marked with the red colour asterisk symbol (*) and until
        all mandatory fields are entered, n ext button should be disabled.</li>
    <li>Contact Name &amp; Account Name will be auto populated as Hyperlinks. The selected Service Type is shown as the
        text field.</li>
    <li><strong> Sold To: </strong> All the ‘Customer CMF’ records which are related to the conatct which have a related
        ‘Customer Partner’ record (with role code: AG) can be selected as valid sold to.</li>
    <li>For selecting Sold To, we have a wild card search functionality which makes it easy to search and get the
        required CMF value instead of going through all the values in a dropdown.</li>
    <li>Based on the Selected Sold To Value, all other data will be fetched for other dropdowns.</li>
    <li>When Sold To is selected, all the other details are auto populated based on the selected ‘Sold to’ value. Values
        are auto populated based on the most recent case created using that particular ‘Sold To ’.</li>
    <li>All other fields in Request header details are dropdowns, if any dropdown contains a single value, it would be
        auto populated when agent selects a value on dependent dropdown for that dropdown.</li>
    <li>Sold To Address values are determined and populated from the ‘Customer Physical Address’ records which are
        related to selected Sold To CMF having address type as ‘ AG/WE/RG .</li>
    <li>From Agent UI, we can see the address records related to selected Sold To: Go to the sold to ‘Customer CMF
        record’ &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; See the address Type as ‘AG/WE/RG ’. All
        the active addresses would be displayed for user to choose from.</li>
    <li>The available sales areas for the selected Sold To are shown in the “Sales Area”</li>
    <li>(Sales Area= Sales org Code –Sales org Name/Distributional Code-Distribution channel name, e.g.,
        EU02-U.K./02-Industrial Disti ) dropdown.</li>
    <li><strong> Ship To: </strong> All the ‘Customer CMF’ records which are related to the selected sold To and
        selected Sales Area which have a related ‘Customer Partner’ record (with role code : WE) can be selected as
        valid s hip to.</li>
    <li>These values are dependent on the Selected Sold To &amp; Sales Area. Hence, when the Sold To/Sales Area is
        changed the other fields should be refreshed/reset.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="f2ad0303-60f8-4c7f-ca88-69a1a732e0e4" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>We have wildcard search functionality present for ‘Ship To’ field also, which works similar to ‘Sold To’
            search.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
    <li><strong> Remedy: </strong> For Service type “ Admin ” the possible remedy value is ‘Credit ’. It will be auto
        populated in the dropdown.</li>
    <li>The Address available for the selected Sold To/ Ship To are displayed in the dropdown.</li>
    <li>The contacts available for the selected Addresses are displayed in the dropdown.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="07f6762a-032e-7421-9d09-91302f1a7dee" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: Add/Edit/ Delete Contact</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>Customer has the option to add new ‘Sold To Contact or ‘Ship To Contact’ contacts and edit or delete the
                previously existing contacts by selecting ‘Add, Edit and Delete Contact’ option from either ‘Sold To
                Contact or ‘Ship To Contact’ dropdowns respectively.</li>
            <li>While creating new contact record associated to the related address record First Name, Email and Phone
                Number are mandatory fields.</li>
            <li><strong> Return Reason : </strong> These values are determined based on the selected ‘Service Type’ and
                ‘Remedy ’ . Values are fetched from the ‘Customer Return Reasons’ object and displayed in dropdown for
                agent to choose from.</li>
            <li><strong> CIRS Number: </strong> This is the input text where agent need to enter a random number by
                using the format ( <strong> CIxxxx-xxxx ) </strong> where x is any number .</li>
            <li><strong> Description </strong> : Agent can provide the issue details in case notes field.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.7. ">Collection Details</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Agent should be unable to select anything in ‘Collection details’ section as it will be disabled until all the
        required fields in the ‘Request Header Details’ section are filled.</li>
    <li>Once all the required fields in ‘Required header details’ are filled, agent would be able to select ‘Return to
        Customer Address’ value from the dropdown in ‘Collection Details ’. These addresses are determined from the Sold
        To ‘Customer CMF’ record.</li>
    <li><strong> Return to Customer Address </strong> : Options are det ermined and populated from the ‘Customer
        Physical Address’ records which are related to selected Sold To CMF having address type as ‘ Return To Customer
        ’ .</li>
    <li>Agent has search options from the dropdown to select Return to Customer address, can search by Name , Country,
        State &amp; Postal Code</li>
    <li>To see the address records related to selected Sold To: Go to the sold to ‘Customer CMF record’ &gt; Open the
        Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; See the address Type as ‘Return To Customer ’. All the active
        address records would be displayed for agent to choose from.</li>
    <li><strong> Return to Customer Contact </strong> : These contact values are fetched based on the selected ‘Return
        to Customer Address.</li>
    <li>To see the contact records related to selected ‘Return to Customer Address’ : Go to the sold to ‘Customer CMF
        record’ &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; Open the selected ‘Return To Customer’
        address record &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Physical Address Contacts. All the active contact records would be
        displayed for agents to choose from.</li>
    <li><strong> Freight Type: </strong> Once ‘Return to Customer Address’ is selected, Freight type values are
        determined and populated from <strong> ‘Sales Freight Determination Matrix ’ </strong> .
        <ul>
            <li><strong> Sales Freight Determination Matrix: </strong> Freight Determination is fetched from matrix
                based on below parameters, record from the matrix with least priority number and matching criteria is
                fetched
                <ul>
                    <li><strong> Service Type </strong></li>
                    <li><strong> Remedy Type </strong></li>
                    <li><strong> Country </strong></li>
                    <li><strong> Return Reason </strong></li>
                    <li><strong> Geography </strong></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>The values are populated from filtering the matrix records by passing Remedy, Service Type, Return Reason, Geo,
        Country (RTC Address Country) fields in the matrix. If no record is found, we exclude Country and fetch the
        record. If still no record is found, we exclude Return Reason and fetch the record.
        <ul>
            <li><strong> Freight Type-IMF (Intel Managed Freight) : </strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>If the customer selects the freight type as IMF (Intel Managed Freight), then all collection
                        details fields are mandatory to proceed further.</li>
                    <li>After selecting the Collection Address, the collection date field is enabled, and date is auto
                        populated.</li>
                    <li><strong> Collection Date </strong> is auto populated based on <strong> Geo Lead Time Matrix
                        </strong> for IMF.</li>
                    <li>For APAC / APJ - 5 days are considered as ‘Lead Time’. Here the 5 th day from current day/ case
                        creation day will be auto populated in the collection date. Apart from that the 4 th day would
                        be enabled for Customer to choose from and the next 8 days would also be enabled for a total of
                        10 enabled days. These dates are all excluding holidays and weekends.</li>
                    <li>For all other regions – ‘Lead Time’ is 3 days. Therefore, 3 rd day from current day would be
                        auto populated, 2 nd day would be enabled along with the next 8 days succeeding ‘Lead Time’
                        excluding holidays &amp; weekends.</li>
                    <li>Example- Let Case creation date is 14 th Mar 2023, the date auto populated for Geo APJ would be
                        22 nd Mar 2023 if there is no holiday for the selected collection Address. If there is holiday
                        for that country on 22 nd Mar 2023, then it would be auto populated as 23 rd Mar 2023.</li>
                    <li><strong> Incoterm Determination: </strong></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    When freight type is IMF, Incoterm value is determined by checking for the exact matching record by passing Remedy,
    Service Type, Return Reason, Geo, Country( Collection Address Country) fields to ‘Incoterm Determination Matrix ’.
    If no record is found, we exclude Country and fetch the record. If still no record is found, we exclude Return
    Reason and fetch the record.
</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong> Freight Type-CRF ( Customer Routed Freight) : </strong>
        <ul>
            <li>If the user selects the freight type as CRF (Customer Routed Freight), the collection date, Return to
                Customer address &amp; Return to customer contact fields are mandatory to proceed further.</li>
            <li><strong> Collection date </strong> will auto-populate to the current day/case creation day as soon as
                the user selects freight type as “CRF” and all the succeeding days would be enabled for the Customer to
                choose from including holidays and weekends.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="7a0358aa-3796-42f0-f089-7a4833583785" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>For IMF, <strong> ‘Collection date’ </strong> would be reset if the case is edited next day .</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
    <li><strong> Collection Address: </strong> Collection address and collection contact fields are only mandatory if
        Freight type is selected as IMF. Collection address values are determined and fetched similar to ‘Return to
        Customer Address’ values.</li>
    <li>The options are det ermined and populated from the ‘Customer Physical Address’ records which are related to
        selected Sold To CMF having address type as ‘ Collection ’ .</li>
    <li>Agent have search option to select Collection address from the dropdown , can search by Name , Country, State
        &amp; Postal Code .</li>
    <li>Also, the addresses are filtered based on the Geo value of the selected Return to customer address .</li>
    <li><strong> Collection Contact: </strong> These contacts are fetched based on the selected ‘Collection Address ’.
    </li>
    <li>To see the contact records related to selected ‘Collection Address’ : Go to the sold to ‘Customer CMF record’
        &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; Open the selected ‘ Collection Address’ record
        &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Physical Address Contacts. All the active contacts would be displayed for agent
        to choose from.</li>
    <li><strong> Origin Bond: </strong>
        <ul>
            <li>If the selected RTC/Collection Address is belongs to India/ China then only User can see the Origin
                Bonded option in UI &amp; t his value is selected as ‘ Non-Bonded ’ by default. Customer can select
                ‘Bonded’ value according to the requirements.</li>
            <li>If the selected RTC/Collection Address is not belongs to India/ China then Origin Bonded option is not
                visible in UI &amp; by default it will consider as ‘ Non-Bonded ’</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong> Return Location: </strong> Return location value is determined from ‘Sales Return Location Matrix’ by
        using the selected Remedy, Service Type, Sold To CMF, Bonded Zone Indicator, Country( IMF- Collection Country,
        CRF - RTC Country)</li>
    <li>If no match is found with above combination, then Sold To CMF is excluded and Return Location value fetched
        again.</li>
    <li>If no match is found it’s a hard stop and agent is notified by relevant error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="90780a2e-041c-3084-b480-1b23300322b0" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: Add/Edit/ Delete Address</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>Agent has the option to add new ‘Return to Customer’ or ‘Collection’ address and edit or delete the
                previously existing addresses by selecting ‘Add, Edit and Delete Address’ option from either ‘Return to
